@startuml sequence_autocomplete
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Autocomplete — Type, Fetch, Keyboard Navigate

actor Visitor
participant "search.js" as JS
participant "Dropdown\n(role=listbox)" as DD
participant "Suggestions API" as API

Visitor -> JS: keyup — value = "clean ar"
JS -> JS: clearTimeout(debounceTimer)
JS -> JS: value.length=8 >= 2 → setTimeout(200ms)

JS -> JS: 200ms elapsed
JS -> JS: abort previous fetch (AbortController)
JS -> API: fetch('/api/public/articles/suggestions?q=clean+ar')
API --> JS: [{title, slug, titleHighlighted}, ...] (≤8)

JS -> DD: Clear and repopulate role=option items
JS -> JS: input.setAttribute('aria-expanded','true')
JS -> JS: input.setAttribute('aria-activedescendant','')

Visitor -> JS: ArrowDown key
JS -> DD: option[0].focus(); aria-activedescendant=option[0].id

Visitor -> JS: ArrowDown key
JS -> DD: option[1].focus()

Visitor -> JS: Enter on option[1]
JS -> Browser: location.href = '/articles/{slug}'

note right of Visitor
  Escape → dropdown closes,\n  focus returns to input, value preserved.
  Click outside → dropdown closes.
  ArrowUp on first item → focus back to input.
end note

@enduml
